<subSubSection id="2A352615A769CF560FC351C464E86160" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A6501B309DB9F880C91A38F8A43D243D" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Berlese (1910) created 
<taxonomicName id="615F01FB96FDA3D7ABBE629E12B197F6" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmochthoniidae" genus="Cosmochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Heterochthonius">Heterochthonius</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="8C2E4583D552C61AEA7E02558E00B76E" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmochthoniidae" genus="Cosmochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cosmochthonius</taxonomicName>
; he mentioned the simple dorsal hairs and the long tarsi as differential characters. Ewing (1917, p. 125) already regarded 
<taxonomicName id="D8A690FBBF6D898FD0B401A85A723692" class="Arachnida" family="Heterochthoniidae" genus="Heterochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heterochthonius</taxonomicName>
as a separate genus, which opinion was established by Grandjean (1928) in his detailed description of 
<taxonomicName id="384D0DEA8A1A2683CFA3D8E9B5EFC73B" class="Arachnida" family="Heterochthoniidae" genus="Heterochthonius" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbus">H. gibbus</taxonomicName>
, the type species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
